  **3. Make sure `backend/__init__.py` exists** — I can see it does from your screenshot, so you're good there.
  
  **4. Move your `requirements.txt` to the root** — you have one inside `backend/` but Vercel needs it at the project root. You already have one at root so just make sure it has all the dependencies.
  
  Your final root structure should look like:
  ```
  /api
    index.py        ← new
  /backend
  /frontend
  vercel.json       ← new
  requirements.txt  ← already exists
  main.py           ← can leave or delete, Vercel won't use it